ilkworms in Shadeweaver Thicket.<br><br>Third quest is getting the gloves, 2 claws from young rockhoppers and foraged fasteners and placing them in stitching kit to make claws. They are 6/37 I believe and are H2H.<br><br>Was extremely late when I was doing these so sorry if they are kinda odd, but that is all I can remember right now accept after you finish your innitiate quests with Poren she sends you to Marhon Sood to turn in a seal, once you have done that you have to goto Kery Miann with a map and give that to her. When you give her the map she says to take this knife (she gives you it) and cut two strips from high quality rockhopper hides. Tailoring is required for all these first quests. I completed that and you turn in the two strips with your two claws and now I have claws that are 7/28 +1str +1dex<br><br>Basically if you take the time to go through the quests your H2H weapons get better and better. Anyway, hope that helps alittle. <br><br>*From Noke Arrier of the Message Boards*<br><br>Useable Shield <br><br>Hail the master smith (merchant) in the armory (the building Kagazz is standing in the alcove of). Tell him, &quot;I am looking for work&quot;. He'll go through some scripted text, ask him, &quot;What broodlings?&quot; Buy the Carapace Shield Frame from him (looks like a shield, scroll down past all the molds).<br>Once you have the frame (it's an 8-slot pack), go out into Shadeweaver's Thicket and kill the Cht'thk Broodlings (little rhino-beetles). Get eight of their carapaces, combine in the pack. Voila, you now have a 4AC 4SV Disease shield! Since we can't dual wield till level 17, we might as well put something in the secondary slot.<br><br>BTW, check the vendors near Shar Vahl (in Shadeweaver's Thicket, to the north past the trainee tents, first building past the banker) for the carapaces. Most people simply sell carapaces to the merchants, and these can often be found for sale. Just a little over 3sp each to buy. <br> <p></p><i></